Investor FAQs
When was Beng Kuang Marine Limited listed?
The company was incorporated as Beng Kuang Marine Pte Ltd in 15 December 1994. Beng Kuang Marine Limited was listed on 15 October 2004.

What business is Beng Kuang Marine Limited in?
Beng Kuang Marine Limited service offerings includes corrosion prevention relating to the repair of ships and other ocean bound vessels primarily in Singapore and Indonesia. The company operates through four business divisions, namely; Corrosion Prevention, Infrastructure Engineering, Supply & Distribution and Shipping. The Corrosion Prevention division provides services which includes blasting and painting as part of ship repair, ship conversion and ship building activities in the marine, offshore and oil & gas industries. It also offers corrosion prevention services for steel work structures and piping modules of oil and jack up rigs. The Infrastructure Engineering Division specializes in the provision of turnkey engineering services ranging from planning , project management to implementation including fabrication, testing, installation and pre-commissioning of steel work modules and structures primarily for customers in the oil & gas industry. The Supply & Distribution Division supplies hardware, tools and other equipment under the Master brand name, for use in the marine, construction, oil & gas industries. The Shipping Division fabricates and charter vessels ranging from tugs, barges and livestock carriers.

How many staff does the Group employ?
Beng Kuang Marine employs over 2000 staff in Singapore & Batam, Indonesia.

What ticker symbol is Beng Kuang Marine Limited?
Beng Kuang Marine Limited is traded under the ticker symbol 5MC.

Which securities exchange is Beng Kuang Marine Limited listed on?
Beng Kuang Marine Limited is listed on the Mainboard of the Singapore Exchange.

What is the number of outstanding shares issued?
The total number of outstanding shares issued is 540,041,625 as of 17 February 2011.

What is the market capitalisation of Beng Kuang Marine Limited?
Beng Kuang Marine Limited's market capitalisation was about S$92.9 million at the mid of January 2012.

What is Beng Kuang Marine Limited fiscal year end?
Beng Kuang Marine Limited operates on the calendar year hence our fiscal year ends December 31.

When does Beng Kuang Marine Limited release its results?
The results are released every quarterly typically in the month of May, August, November and February.

What stake does Labroy Marine Pte Ltd hold in Beng Kuang Marine Limited's?
Labroy Marine Pte Ltd owns approximately 26.98% as of 11 March 2011.

How is the Board of Directors appointed?
There is a formal and transparent process for the appointment of the Board of Directors. The Board's Nominating Committee makes recommendations on all board appointments based on a set of stringent and objective criteria.


What is the total number of ordinary shares issued?
The total number of ordinary shares issued is at 540,041,625 as of 11 March 2011.


How can I obtain a copy of Beng Kuang Marine Limited's annual report?
You may view all our past annual reports online on our Annual Reports and Proxy page.

Where can I get past financial information of Beng Kuang Marine Limited's?
Past financial information of BKM can either be obtained from the Mainboard of the Singapore Exchange or BKM's past annual report based on the specific year.

When do shareholders typically receive annual report and when is your annual general meeting?
Shareholders typically receive Beng Kuang Marine's annual report in early April and our annual general meeting will be held sometime early into the 2nd quarter of the year.












